---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Breadcrumbs from '../../components/Breadcrumbs.astro';
import CTABlock from '../../components/CTABlock.astro';
import { business, BASE } from '../../data/business';
import { postBySlug, postsBySlugs, RELATED_POSTS } from '../../data/posts';
import RelatedPosts from '../../components/RelatedPosts.astro';

const post = postBySlug('flat-pack-assembly-east-ayrshire')!;
const relatedPosts = postsBySlugs(RELATED_POSTS[post.slug] ?? []).slice(0, 3);
const siteUrl = business.siteUrl.replace(/\/$/, '');
const url = `${siteUrl}/blog/${post.slug}/`;
const ogImage = `${siteUrl}${post.ogImage}`;

const articleSchema = {
  '@context': 'https://schema.org',
  '@type': 'Article',
  '@id': `${url}#article`,
  headline: post.title,
  description: post.description,
  inLanguage: 'en-GB',
  datePublished: post.date,
  dateModified: post.date,
  author: {
    '@type': 'Person',
    name: post.author,
    worksFor: { '@id': `${siteUrl}/#business` },
  },
  publisher: { '@id': `${siteUrl}/#business` },
  image: [ogImage],
  mainEntityOfPage: url,
  articleSection: 'Flat-pack assembly',
  keywords: [post.keyword, 'IKEA assembly Kilmarnock', 'Argos flat pack Cumnock', 'Wayfair assembly KA5', 'flat pack fitter East Ayrshire'],
  wordCount: post.wordCount,
  about: { '@type': 'Place', name: 'East Ayrshire, Scotland' },
};
---
<BaseLayout
  title={`${post.title} | Sorn Handyman Services`}
  description={post.description}
  canonicalPath={`/blog/${post.slug}/`}
  ogImage={ogImage}
  extraSchema={articleSchema}
>
  <Breadcrumbs trail={[
    { name: 'Home', href: `${BASE}/` },
    { name: 'Blog', href: `${BASE}/blog/` },
    { name: post.title },
  ]} />

  <article class="container-x py-10 lg:py-14 max-w-3xl">
    <header>
      <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center gap-2 text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider text-amber-600">
        <span>{post.area}</span>
        <span aria-hidden class="text-navy-900/20">·</span>
        <span class="text-navy-900/60">{post.readMinutes} min read</span>
        <span aria-hidden class="text-navy-900/20">·</span>
        <time datetime={post.date} class="text-navy-900/60">{post.dateDisplay}</time>
      </div>
      <h1 class="mt-4 font-serif text-4xl md:text-5xl font-black text-navy-900 leading-tight">
        {post.title}
      </h1>
      <p class="mt-5 text-lg text-navy-900/75">
        What actually turns up in East Ayrshire kitchens and bedrooms in 2026
        — IKEA PAX and BILLY, Argos bunk beds, Wayfair L-desks, Dunelm
        sideboards — the brands that go together clean, the ones that fight
        you, and honest price bands by item.
      </p>
    </header>

    <div class="prose-sorn mt-8 text-lg cv-auto">
      <p>
        Every week we open boxes across
        <a href={`${BASE}/areas/cumnock/`}>Cumnock</a>,
        <a href={`${BASE}/areas/mauchline/`}>Mauchline</a>,
        <a href={`${BASE}/areas/galston/`}>Galston</a> and the rest of the
        KA5, KA17 and KA18 patch. Different brands, different tricks. This
        is the honest version of what we see most on the
        <a href={`${BASE}/services/flat-pack-assembly/`}>flat-pack assembly</a>
        round in East Ayrshire, how long each one takes, and what it costs
        to have someone sensible put it together rather than fight it
        yourself on a Saturday.
      </p>

      <h2>What we see most — by brand</h2>

      <h3>IKEA — still 60% of everything we build</h3>
      <p>
        PAX wardrobes, BILLY bookcases, KALLAX cubes, MALM chests, HEMNES
        beds and the full range of kids’ furniture. IKEA is well-engineered
        flat-pack: dowels are consistent, cam-locks seat clean, and the
        instructions are genuinely good. A competent handyman builds IKEA
        roughly 20% faster than the brand’s own estimate because we know
        which steps overlap. The common mistake on a DIY PAX is covered in
        the dedicated <a href={`${BASE}/blog/flat-pack-assembly-ayr/`}>Ayr
        PAX guide</a>.
      </p>

      <h3>Argos — bunk beds and the occasional wardrobe</h3>
      <p>
        Argos flat-pack lands hardest around school holidays when East
        Ayrshire parents buy a new bunk for the second child. The
        single-over-single bunk is about 90 minutes to build properly,
        with every bolt checked to torque and the ladder bracket hit at
        the right angle. Argos timber is softer than IKEA — over-tightening
        splits the end grain — so torque matters. We see more partially
        built, giving-up calls on Argos bunks than on any other single
        item.
      </p>

      <h3>Wayfair — L-shaped desks and flat-pack sofas</h3>
      <p>
        Wayfair stock varies wildly because it is a marketplace. The big
        L-desks and gaming-station setups are usually two hours and turn
        out fine. The Wayfair flat-pack sofas are where it gets ugly —
        some are clever, some have feet that thread into MDF and strip on
        the first tighten. If you send us the product name before you
        buy, we will tell you honestly whether it is worth the money
        or whether the neighbouring Dunelm item will be stronger.
      </p>

      <h3>Dunelm and B&Q — wardrobes, TV units, dressers</h3>
      <p>
        Dunelm’s own-brand flat-pack is underrated. The timber is thicker
        than Wayfair and the hinges are proper soft-close. B&Q fitted-
        wardrobe kits are fine but install time doubles because they are
        built against the wall with scribe pieces. Price that in if you
        are comparing.
      </p>

      <h3>Oak Furnitureland and Next — rare but worth noting</h3>
      <p>
        Both sell semi-assembled hardwood. Turn up, bolt a top to a base,
        fit drawer runners, done. Forty-five-minute jobs, usually £40.
        If you want the shortest assembly time for the money, these are
        the brands. For built-in runs and alcove shelving we move into
        <a href={`${BASE}/services/joinery/`}>proper joinery</a> work
        instead — different skill, different price band.
      </p>

      <h2>Honest price bands across East Ayrshire</h2>
      <p>
        Same flat-pack pricing we use in
        <a href={`${BASE}/areas/ayr/`}>Ayr</a>. No call-out fee anywhere
        in KA5, KA17, KA18, KA1 or KA3:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>£40</strong> — small items. IKEA LACK, MALM bedside, KALLAX 2×2, Argos single desk, Oak Furnitureland semi-assembled.</li>
        <li><strong>£60–£80</strong> — mid-size. IKEA MALM 6-drawer, Dunelm TV unit, Argos single-over-single bunk, Wayfair office desk.</li>
        <li><strong>£80–£120</strong> — large. Double PAX with standard doors, B&Q fitted-wardrobe single unit, double bunk, sideboard with dowelled back panel.</li>
        <li><strong>£120–£180</strong> — full room. Triple PAX with sliding doors, Wayfair L-desk with hutch, HEMNES double bed with all drawers, large dresser.</li>
        <li><strong>£180+</strong> — multi-item visits. Usually a kids’ bedroom or an office fit-out in one afternoon. Bundled, cheaper per item than separate visits.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        See <a href={`${BASE}/pricing/`}>the full pricing page</a> for the
        handyman hourly rate, the half-day rate and what’s included in a
        multi-item visit.
      </p>

      <h2>Two items that cost more than you expect</h2>

      <h3>Wardrobes with sliding mirror doors</h3>
      <p>
        Any sliding-door wardrobe — IKEA PAX, B&Q sliders, Sharps-style
        copies — needs the frame perfectly level before the doors go on.
        Older houses in
        <a href={`${BASE}/areas/auchinleck/`}>Auchinleck</a>,
        <a href={`${BASE}/areas/catrine/`}>Catrine</a> and rural KA5
        often drop 10mm across the footprint. That is an extra 20 minutes
        of shimming and £10 of plastic shims. It is the difference between
        sliding doors that glide and sliding doors that bounce.
      </p>

      <h3>Bunk beds with torque-sensitive bolts</h3>
      <p>
        The bolts holding a bunk ladder to the frame are the single most
        important fastening in any child’s bedroom. Over-tighten and you
        crack the timber. Under-tighten and the ladder wobbles in a week.
        We use a torque driver on those, not a battery impact. That’s
        five minutes of extra care that matters.
      </p>

      <h2>What we bring that a DIY attempt doesn’t</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>A proper stud finder.</strong> We anchor into stud where possible, never into plasterboard alone.</li>
        <li><strong>Shim packs.</strong> Older East Ayrshire floors dip. Shims are cheap insurance.</li>
        <li><strong>The full fixing kit.</strong> Dot-and-dab anchors, timber screws, masonry plugs, metal plasterboard butterflies — all in the van.</li>
        <li><strong>A torque driver.</strong> Particleboard has one torque. Solid wood has another. Getting it right matters.</li>
        <li><strong>Disposal.</strong> Every scrap of packaging out of the house. We pay the tip fee.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>FAQ</h2>

      <h3>Can you quote before I buy the flat-pack?</h3>
      <p>
        Yes, and we recommend it. Send the product link on WhatsApp and
        we will tell you the assembly band and flag any known pitfalls
        for that SKU. Quicker than building it and finding out.
      </p>

      <h3>Do you cover all of East Ayrshire?</h3>
      <p>
        Yes — KA1 Kilmarnock, KA5 Sorn and Mauchline, KA17 Galston and
        Newmilns, KA18 Cumnock and Auchinleck, KA4 Muirkirk, plus the
        South Ayrshire side (KA7 Ayr, KA9 Prestwick, KA10 Troon, KA12
        Irvine). Nothing is too remote.
      </p>

      <h3>Same-day slots for a single item?</h3>
      <p>
        Usually, yes. For a single flat-pack in East Ayrshire we can
        often come the same afternoon if you ring before 11am.
      </p>

      <h3>Do you build outdoor flat-pack too — sheds and gazebos?</h3>
      <p>
        Yes. Sheds, metal gazebos, outdoor playhouses, trampolines. Pricing
        is by item — send a photo of the box.
      </p>

      <h3>What if I already started and it is in a heap?</h3>
      <p>
        Rescue jobs are the same price as a fresh build. We will unpick
        the worst, straighten what is salvageable, and tell you honestly
        if a panel is split and needs re-ordered.
      </p>

      <p>
        Box on the living-room floor and second thoughts kicking in? Send
        us a photo. Firm price back inside an hour, built the same week
        across East Ayrshire.
      </p>

      <div class="not-prose mt-10 rounded-2xl border border-navy-900/10 bg-navy-50/50 p-6">
        <p class="text-sm text-navy-900/60">Written by</p>
        <p class="mt-1 font-serif text-xl font-bold text-navy-900">{post.author}</p>
        <p class="mt-2 text-navy-900/75 text-sm">{post.authorBio}</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </article>

  <RelatedPosts posts={relatedPosts} eyebrow="Keep reading" heading="Related posts" variant="tinted" />

  <CTABlock
    heading="Flat-pack in a heap? We build, we don't guess."
    sub="WhatsApp a photo of the box — firm price back inside an hour, built this week across East Ayrshire."
    location="East Ayrshire"
  />
</BaseLayout>
